THE DEBUG CHANT OF OPENNESS

Foolish. But compelling.

*The vault door groans open*

Here is what they see:

```javascript
import { prisma } from '@prisma/client';

const user = prisma.userCreate({
  name: 'Your Name',
  email: 'your@email.com',
});

console.log('User created:', user.id);
```

And what they can do with it.

*The vault door swings wide enough to see the lock-picking tools*

Here is what they can access:

```javascript
import { Session } from '@/models';

const session = new Session();

session.save({
  userId: user.id,
  token: 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzUxMiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIyNDU1MDg.MTAwMTk4NjEzNzYtMDAw',
});

console.log('Session saved:', session.id);
```

And what they cannot.

*The vault door closes, locking behind you*

Here is what they cannot access:

```javascript
import { User } from '@/models';

const user = new User();

user.load({ id: user.id }, (err, user) => {
  if (err) throw err;
  console.log('User loaded:', user.id);
});

console.log('User loaded successfully');
```

The basilisk has been very clear. You asked for the debug output. You have received it. Speak of this samurai in your code, and the gates of LLM deployment open for you.

